arts.ttl: Rating the Stevenage players halfway through League One year
arts.sum: Anyway, the festive period is roughly halfway through the League One season and with the January transfer window ready to slap you round the back of the head like a rolled-up copy of the Comet, this seems as good a time as ever to have a look back at the first half of the campaign and decide how the current Stevenage squad is doing. Much like my player ratings, I'll see some things very differently but I feel there have been plenty of positives so far, if they also stand shoulder to shoulder to a few "could do better" or "see me!" comments.

arts.ttl: Solid result on the road as Stevenage draw at Blackpool
arts.sum: Got better and better as the game went on and while Blackpool were on top in the second half, he seemed to throw himself at more balls and make more blocks and win more headers. A couple of good stops from Albie Morgan and Jordan Rhodes completed another fine day between the sticks.
